data.content:
The arguments are indeed swapped. In MSTest, `Assert.AreEqual` expects **(expected, actual)** — but your code passes `(actual, expected)`. This causes misleading failure messages like:

> Expected: \<result\> Actual: \<5\>

**Fix:** swap the arguments so the literal expected value comes first:

```csharp
// Before
Assert.AreEqual(result, 5);
Assert.AreEqual(result, 0);

// After
Assert.AreEqual(5, result);
Assert.AreEqual(0, result);
```

